	<p>It&#8217;s rare that I agree with an entire post.</p>
<p>I think all of your points are valid and make sense depending on what someone wants to do with their company.</p>
<p>The one I would add is never stop being a start-up. Always look at what your strengths are and adjust your offering/strategy accordingly. Always stay hungry.</p>
<p>And just because you get succesful dont stop bootstrapping. </p>
<p>Building Valhalla will not help your company.</p>
<p>OK, maybe that was more than one.</p>
<p>Thanks again for the great post.</p>
