		<div class="comment" id="comment-6102">
	<p><cite>Comment by <a href='http://www.themoleskin.com' rel='external nofollow'>Kelsey Ruger</a> &#8212; May 04 2006 @ <a href="#comment-6102">11:11 am</a></cite> </p>

			
	<p>It&#8217;s amazing how many people don&#8217;t get pricing. I have found several things to be true over the years in different roles. 1) If you provide a good service people will pay the price. 2) People attribute more value to higher priced services, even if this is not always true. 3) Pricing your service too low costs more than the additional revenue you miss out on. This is one of the reasons I think sales or retail experience is good for everyone. Both teach you not be be afraid to ask to for more money, particularly if it is deserved. Good post.</p>
	</div>

