		<div class="comment" id="comment-6206">
	<p><cite>Comment by <a href='http://www.notjustcricket.com' rel='external nofollow'>RJ</a> &#8212; May 05 2006 @ <a href="#comment-6206">9:18 am</a></cite> </p>

			
	<p><b>@ Derek</b></p>
<p>One very good source for &#8216;freelance&#8217; programmers, coders, whizzkids is <a href="http://www.rentacoder.com" rel="nofollow"> Rent A Coder </a>. I know, the name sounds very much like the &#8220;Acme Emporium&#8221; of the RoadRunner cartoons fame. But the site, the process, payments etc are well-supervised. And the price/&#8217;project&#8217; is much cheaper - if bootstrapping is the idea!.</p>
<p>I had a quote of approx $700 to create a blog as per my friend&#8217;s very particular specification (I was helping her out!), from a local design outfit. I put this out to Rent A Coder and the best quote I received was, from an accomplished (but working out of Phillipines) coder/designer, $100 all inclusive. It&#8217;s worth a look.</p>
<p>~RJ</p>
	</div>

